properties.info:
Bình Thạnh
Vietnamese urban district
Bình Thạnh is a district of Ho Chi Minh City in Vietnam. As of 2017, the district had a population of 490,618 and a total area of 21 km². The name of the district was formed from the names of two wards in the old Gò Vấp District, Bình Hòa and Thạnh Mỹ Tây.
Area: 20.8 km²
Population: 490,618 (2017)

properties.display_name: Thu Duc District, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
properties.info:
District 5 (Quận 5)
Vietnamese urban district
District 5 is anchored by Chinatown (Chợ Lớn), with hole-in-the-wall eateries serving dumplings, noodles, and roasted meat dotting its narrow back streets. Cultural landmarks include the 18th-century Bà Thiên Hậu Temple, known for its intricately carved roof, and peaceful Tam Son Pagoda. Vendors sell local produce and spices at sprawling Bình Tây Market, while An Đông Market offers textiles and handicrafts.
Area: 4.27 km²
Population: 187,510 (2018)

properties.name: Phu Nhuan
properties.info:
Phú Nhuận
Vietnamese urban district
Phú Nhuận is a laid-back residential district around sprawling Gia Dinh Park, with its landscaped lawns, jogging paths, and kids’ play areas. Traditional beer-and-snail eateries sit alongside upscale Vietnamese restaurants, while street food kiosks offer steamed rice rolls and soupy noodles. Stalls in Phu Nhuan market are piled high with local produce and seafood, and family-run shops sell clothing and knick-knacks.

properties.display_name: Tan Binh District, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
properties.name: Tan Binh
properties.info:
Tan Binh (Tân Bình)
Vietnamese urban district
Tân Bình is an urban district of Hồ Chí Minh City, Vietnam. The city's international airport is situated in the district. It consists of 15 wards, from Ward 1 to Ward 15. It occupies 22.38 km². In the 2004 census, 397,569 people were recorded as living there. 2005 figures estimate that the population fell to 394,281.
Area: 22.38 km²
Population: 470,350 (2018)

properties.display_name: District 3, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
properties.info:
District 3 (Quận 3)
Vietnamese urban district
District 3 owes its buzz to a lively dining scene, with hip cafes serving inventive coffee drinks, trendy modern Vietnamese restaurants, and low-key noodle eateries. Street food kiosks dot local hangout spots like Turtle Lake and nearby Le Van Tam Park. The War Remnants Museum documents the Vietnam and Indochina wars through photos and weaponry, while 19th-century Tân Định Church is known for its pink facade.
Area: 4.9 km²
Population: 196,433 (2018)

properties.display_name: District 1, Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam
properties.info:
District 1 (Quận 1)
Vietnamese urban district
Buzzing District 1 is home to the Independence Palace, a former presidential home offering tours of its war rooms, and the 19th-century Notre Dame Cathedral. The Hồ Chí Minh City Museum houses local maps and historical photos, and the Fine Arts Museum shows contemporary Vietnamese work. Food kiosks and handicraft stalls fill Ben Thanh Market, while Phạm Ngũ Lão Street is known for its backpacker bars and hostels.
Area: 7.721 km²
Population: 205,180 (2018)

Vietnamese urban district

Gò Vấp
Vietnamese urban district
Gò Vấp is a district of Ho Chi Minh City. Since the 80s, it has undergone significant urbanization. It is larger than most of the other districts. A high urbanization rate has made Gò Vấp become one of the three districts that has high population growth in the city.
Area: 20 km²
Population: 663,313 (2017)
